  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>By default, RepairQ includes a built-in notification trigger for manually emailing receipts from a ticket. This feature ensures that customers receive essential information, enhancing communication and customer satisfaction. To email a receipt, the following must be met:</p><ul><li><p>A Customer Profile must be linked to the ticket.</p></li><li><p>The option \u2018Receive Service Email Notifications\u2019 must be selected in the Customer Profile.</p></li><li><p>The Customer Profile must contain a valid email address.</p><ul><li><p>Please use valid customer email addresses when creating or editing profiles to avoid bounces, spam reports, and potential throttling of your message sending. Using fake or placeholder emails like \u2018<em>na@na.com\u2019</em> can lead to delivery issues by flagging our emails as spam.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3 id=\"EmailaReceipttoaCustomer-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933803736\" rel=\"nofollow\">Send an SMS Ticket Status Notification</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2767290399\" rel=\"nofollow\">Create an Automated SMS Notification</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933344786/Creating+a+Customer+Profile\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933344786\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Create a Customer Profile</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246465/Automated+Notification+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933246465\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Automated Notification Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933803749\" rel=\"nofollow\">Customer Communication Preferences and Marketing List</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933869089\" rel=\"nofollow\">Required Fields for Customer Profiles</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932460196/Send+Notification+Emails+From+Your+Domain\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932460196\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Send Notification Emails From Your Domain</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"EmailaReceipttoaCustomer-SendaReceiptviaEmail\">Send a Receipt via Email</h2><p>On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Tickets</strong>. When viewing the Ticket Queue, you can use the filters to search for an existing ticket or create a new one.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 1.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 2.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%202.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"EmailaReceipttoaCustomer-LinkaCustomertoaTicket(NewTickets)\">Link a Customer to a Ticket (New Tickets)</h3><p>Before saving a ticket or sending a notification, you must attach a customer to the ticket. Use the <strong>Attach Customer button</strong> to add an existing customer or create a new Customer Profile. After linking a customer, you\u2019ll see their details.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: The customer\u2019s profile must have a valid Email Address and \u2018Receive Service Email Notifications\u2019 must be active for the customer to receive notification emails. Use the <strong>Edit Customer button</strong> to add missing info. </p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 3.5.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%203.5.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 3.7.png\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%203.7.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"EmailaReceipttoaCustomer-CustomerDetailsonTickets(TicketViewMode)\">Customer Details on Tickets (Ticket View Mode)</h3><p>The \u2018Customer\u2019 section lists the customer\u2019s contact info. The customer must have a valid email address, for email notifications to be sent successfully.</p><p>If the email address is missing, or you need to update their notification settings, you can edit the ticket and click the <strong>Edit Customer button</strong> to add the missing details.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 3.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Ticket actions are located in the upper-right corner of the ticket. To email the customer with their receipt details, click the <strong>Envelope Icon</strong>. You will receive a notification that the email was successfully queued.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 4.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%204.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 5.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%205.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"EmailaReceipttoaCustomer-NotificationQueue\">Notification Queue</h2><p>To check your outgoing notification queue, use the Navigation Bar to go to <strong>Reports \u2192 Notifications</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 6.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Notifications Summary page, you can view a queue of all outgoing notifications.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 7.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%207.png?api=v2\"></span><p>The table includes columns to help you identify the following details:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Type </strong>- Indicates the type of notification sent. This can either be an automated notification or an announcement.</p></li><li><p><strong>Subject </strong>- Displays the subject or title of the outgoing notification.</p></li><li><p><strong>Message </strong>- Shows a preview of the main content of the enclosed message.</p></li><li><p><strong>Attachment </strong>- Lists any attached files, such as receipts, invoices, etc.</p></li><li><p><strong>Status </strong>- Indicates whether the notification is New (pending) or Sent. Notifications have an approximate 5-minute delay before sending, during which you can cancel a queued message by clicking the <strong>Red X</strong> <strong>Button </strong>next to the notification.</p></li><li><p><strong>To </strong>- Displays the recipient\u2019s email address or SMS phone number.</p></li><li><p><strong>Created At </strong>- A timestamp indicating when the notification was queued.</p></li><li><p><strong>Send At </strong>- For most notifications, this will show an immediate send time. However, automated notifications may be sent on a delay based on the configured settings.</p></li><li><p><strong>Location </strong>- Displays the location that sent the notification.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"EmailaReceipttoaCustomer-EmailReceipt\">Email Receipt</h3><p>Below is an example of the email your customer will receive. Check out our article, <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933246465\" rel=\"nofollow\">Automated Notification Resources</a>, for details including creating, editing, and sending notifications automatically.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Email 8.png\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933672639/Email%208.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
